<br>
The guy in the bottom of the lake in LavaStorm would be a piece of cake if you didn't have to kill him while actually in the lava. FireResist gear/buffs and a good Regen are a must for him. I have usually seen him killed the following way ........ Everybody gets DeadManFloat and head out over the LavaLake. A tracker (Eryl) will stand over the spot where Eejag is and everybody will gather there. Clerics will stay up up top and the dmg dealers will all go straight down and engage Eejag. People will come to the surface for heals and occasionaly a cleric will have to duck under the surface of the lava to throw a heal on the MainAssist. If everything goes well...he will die quickly and not summon you to the bottom of the LavaLake as you try to swim up to the surface to get a heal. If anybody actually dies...it is usually from the Lava and not from the hand of Eejag.<br>
<br>
As far as the guy on the 2nd Isle in PoA goes....Once again I have always seen him killed as a temp &quot;stop off&quot; while on a raid. He is sort of on the tough side as far as the damage he can deal and the amount of HitPoints he has. But he is not usually too much of a problem because there is usually a full Force raid going on. All you usually have to do is convince the raid leader to get everybody the keys and to make a 20 minute stop over.<br>
<br>
Hope that helps...but as always the best advise you can get is from other Monks who have already done the quests and can give you all the fine details.<br>
<br>
